Text: Theoretically, it is the first week of our new project.
The new one and the last in teams.
Practically I have an impression that we are almost after two weeks of the project and do not know when it passed.
We are already after pitch, after the proposal, after the poster preparation.
When?.How??
After experiences during my second project and the listening teams' final presentations at the end of the second projects, I try to be openminded.
But I also communicate straight forward what I think even if I do not agree with some solutions or I would like to explore more another part of the project.
I do not know if it is good or not, but I would like to enjoy this project and focus on the important aspects.
On the other hand, I think that all of us try to be more open especial after Friday's Teacher3's presentation and think about the others.
The real challenge for each person is to admit that she/he does not know something, and everything requires time and will to explore new fields/languages and acceptance from the rest of the team.
I hope that we will find the solution and at least one piece of this project will work.

I have English lessons regularly and I hope that it will help me to communicate difficult matters in a more appropriate way, not only during the project but also for the future in other circumstances.

The teamwork was quite smooth during the last three weeks: the week with the pitch, the mid-sem break (we had meetings through zoom to prepare the questions for the client and the base for the poster) and the official first week.
We had sometimes different opinions but we have come to a consensus or a compromise fast or decided that we will consider this aspect if we have more information or research.
The all parts for communication were set, like Teams, What's up, Trello, GitHub.
It was really so fast and smooth.
Right now we focus on research, communication with our client regularly and programming.Step by step.

Our goals for the next week: 1/prepare and test one part for the team changing and on-call hours (Roro started this part already)2/ prepare low-fidelity prototype of UI and reports3/ for me to explore the Visual Studio - I hope that Gogo shows us how we can use it in an efficient way4/ start prepare high-fidelity prototype of UIÂ 5/ work on uses casesÂ Â  Â The main task for me for the coming week:  to prepare reports mockup and UI for reports.
To explore the Visual Studio and start to learn C# (Bibi will prepare some examples fro the laymenðŸ˜„ ).
Going back to what happened up to this time: We had 9 meetings already:  via zoom, Teams and in person.
What I like is that when we meet we know that this is time for the project.
Even if we are working in silence we know, that each of us works under the piece of the current task for example.
We prepared the pitch, questions to the client, poster.
I did some research on other solutions.
We tried to take advantage of every moment to omit the unnecessarily time-wasting.
Each of us analyses the sources from the client and try to find a piece of the solution.
Teamwork is very hard and we have to look for proper communication way.
But we have to be also assertive to not go crazy.
I admire somebody who can stop and say:  sorry now is time for other stuff, but after of course when this person is engaged strongly in the project.
Sometimes the mind reset is needed for the future brilliant solutions: https: //pl.dreamstime.com/zdj%C4%99cia-stock-kresk%C3%B3wka-ma-pomys%C5%82u-m%C4%99%C5%BCczyzna-image20848883Have a nice week
Overall
